<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910716-0062</DOCNO><DOCID>910716-0062.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Elcor Corp.:   Roofing Products Company   To Post 4th-Quarter Loss</HL><DATE>07/16/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   ELK</CO><MS>INDUSTRIAL (IDU)</MS><IN>BUILDING MATERIALS, CONCRETE, GLASS, PAINT (BLD)</IN><RE>NORTH AMERICA (NME)TEXAS (TX)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   Elcor Corp. said it expects to take additional reservesfor its fourth quarter ended June 30, resulting in a loss ofabout $6.1 million.   The Dallas maker of roofing products said it expects totake a $6.5 million charge reflecting the sale of its GoryAssociated Industries Inc. unit, asset write-downs andadditions to its warranty reserves for a product itdiscontinued in 1985.</LP><TEXT>   For the year, Elcor said it expects to report a net lossof about $15.5 million, reflecting about $9.2 million inreserves and write-downs during the second half of its fiscalyear.   The company said it expects to be profitable in the firstquarter.   In the fourth quarter last year, Elcor had a net loss of$984,000, or 14 cents a share, including a $417,000 reversalof an extraordinary tax benefit. For fiscal 1990, it had netincome of $2.6 million, or 37 cents a share, including a $1.6million gain from a patent infringement award and an $804,000gain from a tax benefit.</TEXT></DOC>